snippet.textDisplay:
It was better than TLJ. But it’s a VERY low bar. Overall, it’s a BAD movie. Here are some problems, while my memory is fresh straight from the theatre:
1. They didn’t explain how Palpatine survived.
2. The healing part is a major plot hole. Obi-Wan could have saved his master.
3. Suddenly Rey is not Mary Sue. She needs training. You are either OP or not, you can not change it.
4. You can just ignore movie 8 now. No consistency with first two movies of the trilogy.
5. If Palpatine was the main villain of the saga, then Anakin was the main hero. They didn’t show him once.
6. If Force ghosts are so powerful, what prevents them from forming a Ghost Batallion?
7. Rey’s force lightning? Seriously ?
8. What prevents Palpatine from coming back again ?
9. You can suck power out of others ? Why didn’t Vader do it to restore his body?

And that’s just on top of my head. If Igive it a thought, I am sure more problems will be remembered . Overall, last season GOT level of storytelling.

snippet.textDisplay: I very much enjoyed this movie, I found it very funny, the action was excellent, and the performances were the best you can get in a Star Wars movie. However I dislike what they did in terms of plot, bringing the emperor back makes the last two films feel out of place and unrelated, as if this movie is the closer for a trilogy that doesn’t exist. I liked the ending and I feel the orange lightsaber symbolises the end of the Jedi/Sith, and the birth of ‘Skywalkers’ as an idea rather than a family, like Batman is. I’m still processing so maybe my opinions will change over time.

snippet.textDisplay: If Abrams had all 3 movies and Rey was always a palpatine then this could have worked out 'possibly'. Star Wars 1-6 is all about the Skywalker fam. Anakin's fall is encapsulated in Episode3 when he has to choose between two father figures (Obi-wan vs Palpatine). Even after Yoda and Obiwan tell Luke that Anakin is gone and only Vader remains, Luke still goes and Vader has his redemption arc. TFA could have introduced us Rey (who had no family that she knows of, abandonment issues) and Kylo who "had THE family" and yet abandoned them. Develop their dichotomy more and Rey feeling connection with Leia, Han and Kylo actively trying to destroy his own connection to them. This movie (cut down and in part) could have been the 8th episode in place Last Jedi and instead of Last Jedi telling Rey she has no parents, you end the 8th episode with the bombshell that she is a Palpatine and that she actually considered joining Kylo (mirroring a 'ben why didn't you tell me' reveal of Luke's parentage). This would have actually given Rey character and a arc in episode 8. Especially if she is good at dark side powers but not at light side. They could have even explored more of Rey trying to choose the light (while being born from a Sith) and Kylo trying to choose dark side while having being born in the light. You could develop more about Finn and the storm trooper brainwashing and Finn and group in Episode8 destroy the brainwashing center and you get some stormtroopers joining Finn and hell, I would be totally fine with Rey being so confused and lost at learning she is a Palpatine that she JOINS Kylo and the first order in Episode 8. A dark side Rey and Kylo at the end of 8, with Leia and the others stuck on the other side would setup a lot of tension and character development. Then in a real episode 9, you could have Palpatine return, develop everything into the final confrontation and it could make some sense. You could even explain that Luke was in hiding because he sensed Palpatine or whatever and that he was actively investigating and doing 'something' but that his attempt to stop Palpatine resulted in losing Kylo, and then he lost Rey and so he has to go with the Leia, and the others to save their 'kids'. Instead we have Episode 8 destroyed Episode 7 and Episode 9 ignored 8 ever existed.

snippet.textDisplay: Her taking Skywalker's name makes total sense.  Why take the name Palpatine, when he killed her parents, and wanted to simply use her for his own purpose?  While Luke and Leia were a real family to her, showed her a place in the universe where she belonged, and gave her direction.  Obviously, she felt more like a Skywalker at this point than a Palpatine.  The only other alternative that would've made sense would be to take the Solo name.  Doing so would mean a name change to Rise of Solo, though.  lol.

snippet.textDisplay: This is confusing... you say this movie is amazing yet go on to say you didn’t like Han Solo being a ghost, didn’t like how Palpatine died, didn’t like how Kylo Ren died, and didn’t like Rey taking the Skywalker name (All very big parts of this film). You say she is weaker than Kylo yet she is stronger than the strongest Star Wars villain?(The whole power of all the Jedi is BS they would of helped Luke in episode 6 over Rey).  You also left out parts that were just as silly like Leia training Rey and being stronger than Luke? You also said it should of been episode 8? Doesn’t sound like you felt it ended everything that well then? And when you say it fixed episode 8 what you meant is they completely ignored it. From what I heard you liked the visuals and all the nostalgia throwbacks but that was about it. Movie sounds like it isn’t that great.😔
